FBIS4-3850 "drchi080_a_94014" FBIS-CHI-94-080 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina XINHUA Reports Developments on Bosnia-Herzegovina UN Warns of Air Strike Following Deadline OW2304224694 Beijing XINHUA in English 2207 GMT 23 Apr 94 OW2304224694 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] United Nations, April 23 (XINHUA) -- U.N. Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali will immediately authorize the use of NATO air strikes against Bosnian Serb Forces if they do not withdraw from a 3-kilometer zone from the center of Gorazde by midnight. "Should the required cease-fire and withdrawal fail to take place by 0001 hours GMT April 24, the secretary-general will immediately authorize the use of air strikes to protect the safe area of Gorazde," Joe Sills, spokesman for the secretary-general, said here this evening.
